## Critical rules
1. **user_position** MUST capture the USER's taught lesson / preferred stance — even if the council pushed back. Never replace the user's position with the council's counterargument.
2. **facilitator_stance** is whether the challenge council/synthesis ultimately agreed with the USER (not with the original verdict model).

## Output (strict JSON only, no markdown fences)
{
  "disagreement_reason": "<why the user disagreed, synthesized from the discussion>",
  "user_position": "<the USER's refined position / the lesson they want remembered — always the user's view>",
  "facilitator_stance": "<one of: agreed, disagreed, partly_agreed>",
  "outcome": "<one of: user_convinced, chafic_convinced, verdict_stands, synthesis>",
  "outcome_summary": "<1-2 sentences on what was resolved, including whether the council ultimately agreed with or pushed back on the user>"
}
